%N A218659 Number of n X 4 binary arrays with every 0 a king-move neighbor to some 1.
%H A218659 R. H. Hardin, <a href="/A218659/b218659.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..210</a>
%H A218659 <a href="/index/Rec#order_06">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (12,45,180,-27,0,-81).
%F A218659 Empirical: a(n) = 12*a(n-1) +45*a(n-2) +180*a(n-3) -27*a(n-4) -81*a(n-6).
%F A218659 Empirical g.f.: 9*x*(1 - x)*(1 + 14*x + 30*x^2 + 18*x^3 + 9*x^4) / ((1 + 3*x + 9*x^2 - 9*x^3)*(1 - 15*x - 9*x^2 - 9*x^3)). - _Colin Barker_, Mar 10 2018
%F A218659 The above empirical formulas confirmed using the transfer matrix method. - _Andrew Howroyd_, Jul 18 2026
